==English==
===Noun===
'''pharaoh'''

# The supreme ruler of ancient Egypt.
# A personification of ancient Egypt i.e. a potential metonym for Ancient Egyptian sovereignty, much like America's "White House" may designate the presidency or encumbered party in it's institutional role; or like the Kremlin may refer to the Russian presidency; or Westminster referring to British political systems.
# A possible phonological mutation introduced by way of Ancient Greek transcription. Ancient Egyptian Language (AEL) ''per-aa'' [''pr-aa'']. From AEL ''pr'' ; meaning dwelling-place, temple or house & the AEL suffix ''-aa''; designating great, spectacular or excellor. Hence ''pr-aa'' or per-aa ; the Great House.  Primary used as a formal address for the sovereign seat of power as personified by the 'king' in an institutional role of Horus son of Osiris.
